 :tx/rationale "Create task: CE-BOOT: Structural bootstrap hypothesis generator at init/first-status time. CONTEXT: At zero knowledge, braid provides zero hypotheses. The file system IS the first generative model. Directory structure, file sizes, import relationships encode project architecture before reading a single line. RATIONALE: The coupled dynamics dK/dt=f(H) require H>0 to start. Bootstrap provides initial H that kicks system off trivial fixed point. APPROACH: (1) Add generate_bootstrap_hypotheses(project_root: &Path) -> Vec<BootstrapHypothesis> to a new module crates/braid-kernel/src/bootstrap_hypotheses.rs. (2) Walk directory tree, collect entries: (relative_path, file_count, total_bytes, extensions). Skip hidden dirs, node_modules, vendor, target, build. (3) Identify packages/modules: directories containing source files. Rank by file_count * total_bytes (size proxy for importance). (4) Parse lightweight import edges if possible: Go imports from 'import' blocks, Rust 'use' from first 50 lines, Python 'import/from' statements, JS require/import. Build adjacency map. (5) Compute centrality: in-degree + out-degree from import graph. (6) Generate hypotheses: Top-5 packages by size*centrality get 'What does {package} do? ({files} files, {KB} KB, imports: {deps})'. Top-3 dependency edges get 'How does {A} interact with {B}? ({A} imports {B})'. Test coverage hypothesis: '{test_files}/{total_files} test coverage by file count'. Entry point hypothesis: '{main_file} is the entry point — trace the dispatch'. (7) Each hypothesis has: question (String), expected_delta_fs (f64, estimated from structural weight), source_path (String), phase (:bootstrap). (8) Store as :hypothesis/bootstrap-{hash} datoms with :hypothesis/question, :hypothesis/expected-delta-fs, :hypothesis/source, :hypothesis/phase = 'structural'. (9) Wire into braid status: when bootstrap hypotheses exist AND F(S) < 0.3, show them as 'Investigation hypotheses:' section BEFORE task recommendations. (10) Wire into braid seed: when bootstrap hypotheses exist, include as orientation instead of braid self-description. (11) As agent explores and records observations covering a hypothesis's package, mark hypothesis as 'explored' (dampening in future guidance). ACCEPTANCE: (A) On Go CLI (62.5K LOC): generates 10+ hypotheses including internal/consistency, internal/storage, internal/search. (B) On braid itself (Rust): generates hypotheses for braid-kernel, braid crates. (C) On empty directory: generates 0 hypotheses gracefully. (D) Hypotheses appear in braid status as primary guidance on fresh store. (E) Hypotheses appear in braid seed orientation section. (F) After agent observes 5+ times in a package, that package's hypothesis is dampened. (G) Generation completes in <500ms for 62K LOC project. FILE: crates/braid-kernel/src/bootstrap_hypotheses.rs (new) + crates/braid/src/commands/status.rs + crates/braid-kernel/src/seed.rs"
